related_questions.question: What is the ignition coil gap on Stihl?
related_questions.title: AI Overview
list: Some Stihl models might have slightly different recommended gaps, so it's always best to consult the specific owner's manual or a Stihl service manual for your equipment.

A good rule of thumb for small engines is the 10-20-30 rule: 0.010 inch for the coil-flywheel gap, 0.020 inch for the points gap (if applicable), and 0.030 inch for the spark plug gap according to one YouTube video.
Improperly set ignition coil gaps can lead to various issues, including hard starting, loss of power, and even damage to the ignition coil.
